## Some Background

As many FIFA Ultimate Team Owner's know, there are both mobile and Web versions of the game in the form of a management application. These applications both have the ability to buy and sell players on the "Transfer Market", and thus make it easy to integrate with scripts programtically, all you need is a little knowledge of the DOM (in the case of the web implementation). In this little tutorial I'll walk you through the code and how it could hypothetically be used to undermine EA's AntiBot system.

This is intended for educational use only.

## The Setup

Here's what you will need to get started:

* Text Editor
* Chrome
* Novice Javascript Knowledge

var scrollLogToBottom = function scrollLogToBottom() {
  var log = $('#progressTransferMarket');
  if (log.length) {
    log.scrollTop(log[0].scrollHeight - log.height());
  }
};
 
scrollLogToBottom();
 
var addMessage = function addMessage(msg) {
  var oldLog = log;
  var n = new Date();
  var m = n.getMinutes();
  m = m < 10 ? "0" + m : m;
  var s = n.getSeconds();
  s = s < 10 ? "0" + s : s;
  var datestamp = `${n.getDate()}-${n.getMonth()+1}-${n.getFullYear()}`;
  var timestamp = `${n.getHours()}:${m}:${s}`;
  var message = "[" + timestamp + "] " + msg + "\n";
  log = oldLog + message;
  $('#progressTransferMarket').val(log);
  scrollLogToBottom();
};
 
 
 
function randomizeMaxPrice() {
  var increment = (Math.round(Math.random() * 10) * 1000)  * (Math.random() > 0.5 ? 100 : (Math.random()> 0.5 ? 10 : 1));
  var randomPrice = Math.random() > 0.5 ? 14000000 + increment : 14000000 - increment;
  return randomPrice;
}

function getDelay(rpm) {
  var intv = (60/rpm);
  var tolerance = intv/4 * (Math.random() * 0.75);
  var direction = Math.random() > 0.5 ? 1 : -1;
  var delay = Math.round(intv + (tolerance * direction));
  return delay * 1000;
};
